Summary:
We are considering HP and Canon, 44" and 60", costing above $5K or $10K.
Ink and paper run us less than $1000/yr. Support costs up to $1000/yr, depending. 
I will do more research yet, here is what i have so far.

Consumables:
Ink and paper costs are the same per sq foot for 44" or 60". The plotters can use narrower paper.
Costs are much lower if we buy from a photo supplier vs staples office supply. The Canon and low end HP cost 25% more for ink

For a full graphics image print, ink used per sq ft is 1.3ml-1.5ml, roughly $0.70 / sqft for ink.
Paper costs vary, plain HP Heavy Coated is .12 / sqft, and HP satin photo paper .24 / sqft.

Text or graphs cost less and less in ink, but we do a lot of graphics. Also there is some ink lost on a large format printer used infrequently (less than daily) to prevent dry ink clogs so deduct a bit.

A 4'x6' conference poster costs $140 at kinkos, but only costs us $20 in ink/paper. Sometimes we have to test and/or reprint for various reasons, probably averaging about 1 discarded print for each good print. If we estimate 20 finished posters / year, that is 40 large prints / yr, that costs
$800 / year for ink and paper.

Support:
The HP plotters offer an on site repair support contract, $520, $600 and $800 / year (for five years). Looks like those support periods overlap warranty, so you might figure the per year cost 20% higher. This is high level support, next day onsite visit when needed, and there may be lower cost support with longer response times. I'll call sales.

HP Z6600 60" = $10360 shipped (+ $4,000 5 year support)   = $14,360
HP Z5400 44" = $6160 shipped (+ $3,000 5 year support)     = $ 9,160
HP Z3200ps 44" = $5171 shipped (+ $2600 5 yr support)      = $ 7.771

Canon iPF9400s 60" = $8822 shipped
Canon iPF8400s 44" = $4745 shipped

Canon support looks excessively high, $1300/yr for phone support, parts, and repair if we ship it in. I am still investigating if there isn't a cheaper, better support available third party.

